      %h2
        devsync
        %a{href: "https://github.com/ciju/devsync"} github.com/ciju/devsync
      %div.description
        A chrome devtools (WebInspector) hack, which allows your css/javascript edits from WebInspector to be saved directly to the localhost files. It was a winner at
        %a{href: "http://developer.yahoo.com/blogs/ydn/posts/2011/08/open-hack-india-they-hacked-we-won-them-over/"} Yahoo! Hacknight. It is a node.js application

  %div.project.redis-proxy
    %div
      %h2
        Redis Proxy
        %a{href: "https://github.com/sreeix/redis-proxy"} github.com/sreeix/redis-proxy
      %div.description
        It is the HAProxy of
        %a{href: "http://redis.io/"} Redis servers.
        Redis-proxy proxies the Redis master-slave(s) farm, and automagically manage the the failures of slaves and master, with zero downtime. Redis Replication dance as it is usually know, is avoided with such a setup.
        %br
        It also lets you scale your redis subsystem by splitting reads to slaves and writes (going to master). It is a big win for scaling and Availability of redis servers. It's published as a node.js module and written in Javascript

